ClzCopy v1.0
Copyright (C) 2014 Chris Poole - chris@hackernet.co.uk

This tool watches a selected portion of the directory tree for updated CLZ files.
When changes are detected in CLZ files, they are copied to the top level selected folder.

In the example filesystem below, select C:\SomeProject as the folder, then whenever the files
bin\FtpExampleLibrary.clz and bin\RSSLibrary.clz are updated, they will be copied into the
C:\SomeProject folder to accompany the usp files, this WILL overwrite the existing clz file.

This is intended to work with the following example directory tree layout, for the example:

C:\SomeProject\
	mycode.smw
	FtpExample.usp
	FtpExampleLibrary.clz
	Rss.usp
	RssLibrary.clz

	FtpExampleLibrary\
		FtpExampleLibrary.sln
		FtpExampleLibrary.csproj
		program.cs
		bin\
			FtpExampleLibrary.clz

	RssLibrary\
		RssLibrary.sln
		RssLibrary\
			RssLibrary.csproj
			Rss.cs
			bin\
				RssLibrary.clz
	

